---
import "../styles/global.css";

const docsUrl = "https://docs.beecrawl.dev/";

const endpoints = [
  {
    method: "POST",
    path: "/scrape",
    title: "Scrape a page",
    description: "Fetch a page and return clean Markdown, metadata, links, HTML, or a screenshot.",
    request: `{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "formats": ["markdown", "links"],
  "use_browser": "auto",
  "timeout_seconds": 30
}`,
    response: `{
  "request_id": "req_123",
  "final_url": "https://example.com",
  "markdown": "# Example Domain...",
  "links": ["https://www.iana.org/domains/example"],
  "metadata": { "status_code": 200, "rendered": false }
}`,
  },
  {
    method: "POST",
    path: "/map",
    title: "Map a site",
    description: "Discover same-site URLs from the sitemap and page links.",
    request: `{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "limit": 100,
  "includeSubdomains": false
}`,
    response: `{
  "request_id": "req_123",
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "links": ["https://example.com/docs"],
  "metadata": { "count": 1 }
}`,
  },
  {
    method: "POST",
    path: "/search",
    title: "Search the web",
    description: "Search by keyword and optionally scrape the returned pages.",
    request: `{
  "query": "thermal interface material suppliers",
  "limit": 5,
  "scrapeOptions": { "formats": ["markdown"] }
}`,
    response: `{
  "requestId": "req_123",
  "data": [{ "url": "https://example.com", "title": "Example" }],
  "metadata": { "total": 1 }
}`,
  },
  {
    method: "POST",
    path: "/extract",
    title: "Extract structured data",
    description: "Turn page content into a predictable JSON object using a field description or schema.",
    request: `{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "schema": {
    "company": "Company name",
    "email": "Contact email"
  }
}`,
    response: `{
  "request_id": "req_123",
  "data": { "company": "Example Inc.", "email": null },
  "metadata": { "provider": "deterministic" }
}`,
  },
];

const asyncEndpoints = [
  ["POST", "/crawl", "Start an asynchronous same-site crawl."],
  ["GET", "/crawl/:id", "Poll status and paginated results."],
  ["DELETE", "/crawl/:id", "Request crawl cancellation."],
  ["POST", "/batch/scrape", "Start a batch scrape for independent URLs."],
  ["GET", "/batch/scrape/:id", "Poll batch status and results."],
  ["DELETE", "/batch/scrape/:id", "Request batch cancellation."],
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="description" content="BeeCrawl API documentation and endpoint reference." />
    <title>API Docs | BeeCrawl</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <nav class="nav shell" aria-label="Primary navigation">
        <a class="brand" href="/"><span class="bee" aria-hidden="true"><span class="bee-wing bee-wing-left"></span><span class="bee-wing bee-wing-right"></span><span class="bee-body">🐝</span></span><span class="brand-copy">BeeCrawl<span class="brand-mark">.</span></span></a>
        <div class="nav-links"><a class="nav-current" href={docsUrl}>API docs</a><a href="https://github.com/jacoobwang/beecrawl">GitHub</a></div>
        <a class="nav-cta" href="https://github.com/jacoobwang/beecrawl">Get started <span aria-hidden="true">-&gt;</span></a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="docs-page">
      <section class="docs-hero">
        <div class="shell docs-hero-inner">
          <p class="kicker">API reference / v0.1</p>
          <h1>Build with <em>BeeCrawl</em></h1>
          <p class="lede">A small, self-hostable API for extracting useful data from the web. All endpoints return JSON and accept a JSON request body.</p>
          <div class="docs-actions"><a class="button button-dark" href="https://github.com/jacoobwang/beecrawl">View source <span aria-hidden="true">-&gt;</span></a><a class="text-link" href={docsUrl}>Open the full docs <span aria-hidden="true">-&gt;</span></a></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="authentication" class="docs-section docs-intro">
        <div class="shell docs-two-column">
          <div><p class="kicker">01 / Getting started</p><h2>One base URL.<br /><em>One header.</em></h2></div>
          <div class="docs-copy"><p>Send your API key in <code>X-Web-Extract-Api-Key</code>, <code>X-Api-Key</code>, or as a bearer token. Authentication is optional when the server is not configured with an API key.</p><pre><code>curl https://api.beecrawl.dev/scrape \\
  -H "X-Web-Extract-Api-Key: YOUR_API_KEY" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"</code></pre><p class="docs-note">Set <code>BEECRAWL_WEB_EXTRACT_API_KEY</code> or <code>WEB_EXTRACT_API_KEY</code> on the API service to require authentication.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="docs-section endpoint-section" aria-labelledby="endpoint-heading">
        <div class="shell"><div class="docs-section-heading"><div><p class="kicker">02 / Core endpoints</p><h2 id="endpoint-heading">The API surface</h2></div><p>Use the native routes for the smallest request and response shapes. Replace the host with your own deployment when self-hosting.</p></div>
          <div class="endpoint-list">
            {endpoints.map((endpoint, index) => <article class="endpoint-card" id={endpoint.path.slice(1)}><div class="endpoint-heading"><span class="endpoint-index">0{index + 1}</span><span class:list={["method", `method-${endpoint.method.toLowerCase()}`]}>{endpoint.method}</span><code>{endpoint.path}</code><h3>{endpoint.title}</h3><p>{endpoint.description}</p></div><div class="endpoint-code"><div><span class="pane-label">Request body</span><pre><code>{endpoint.request}</code></pre></div><div><span class="pane-label">Response body</span><pre><code>{endpoint.response}</code></pre></div></div></article>)}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="docs-section docs-intro async-section">
        <div class="shell docs-two-column"><div><p class="kicker">03 / Async jobs</p><h2>For the bigger<br /><em>workloads</em></h2></div><div class="docs-copy"><p>Crawls and batch scrapes return an <code>id</code> immediately. Poll the matching status endpoint with <code>?offset=0&amp;limit=20</code> to read progress and paginated results.</p><div class="async-table">{asyncEndpoints.map(([method, path, description]) => <div><span class:list={["method", `method-${method.toLowerCase()}`]}>{method}</span><code>{path}</code><span>{description}</span></div>)}</div></div></div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer"><div class="shell footer-inner"><a class="brand" href="/"><span class="bee" aria-hidden="true"><span class="bee-wing bee-wing-left"></span><span class="bee-wing bee-wing-right"></span><span class="bee-body">🐝</span></span><span class="brand-copy">BeeCrawl<span class="brand-mark">.</span></span></a><p>Open-source web data infrastructure.</p><a href="https://github.com/jacoobwang/beecrawl">GitHub</a></div></footer>
  </body>
</html>
